<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 26 at 11:14AM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Scotland, southern
Anson, southeastern Richmond and southern Hoke Counties through 1145
AM EDT...
At 1114 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles north of Chesterfield to near Purvis.
Movement was northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Laurinburg, Rockingham, Wadesboro, Raeford, Hamlet, Maxton, Hoffman,
Antioch, Dobbins Heights and Wagram.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
